wikipedia.ico"/>\n<link rel="search" type="application/opensearchdescription+xml" href="/w/opensearch_desc.php" title="Wikipedia (en)"/>\n<link rel="EditURI" type="application/rsd+xml" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd"/>\n<link rel="license" href="//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/"/>\n<link rel="canonical" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time_value_of_money"/>\n<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//login.wikimedia.org"/>\n<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//meta.wikimedia.org" />\n</head>\n<body class="mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-0 ns-subject page-Time_value_of_money rootpage-Time_value_of_money skin-vector action-view">\t\t<div id="mw-page-base" class="noprint"></div>\n\t\t<div id="mw-head-base" class="noprint"></div>\n\t\t<div id="content" class="mw-body" role="main">\n\t\t\t<a id="top"></a>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="siteNotice" class="mw-body-content"><!-- CentralNotice --></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class="mw-indicators mw-body-content">\n</div>\n\t\t\t<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Time value of money</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="contentSub"></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">\n\t\t\t\t\tJump to:\t\t\t\t\t<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, \t\t\t\t\t<a href="#p-search">search</a>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Economics_of_climate_change_chapter3_discounting_curves.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Economics_of_climate_change_chapter3_discounting_curves.png/220px-Economics_of_climate_change_chapter3_discounting_curves.png" width="220" height="163" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Economics_of_climate_change_chapter3_discounting_curves.png/330px-Economics_of_climate_change_chapter3_discounting_curves.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Economics_of_climate_change_chapter3_discounting_curves.png/440px-Economics_of_climate_change_chapter3_discounting_curves.png 2x" data-file-width="1157" data-file-height="858" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Economics_of_climate_change_chapter3_discounting_curves.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nThe present value of $1,000, 100 years into the future. Curves represent constant discount rates of 2%, 3%, 5%, and 7%.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The <b>time value of money</b> describes the greater benefit of receiving money now rather than later. It is founded on <a href="/wiki/Time_preference" title="Time preference">time preference</a>.</p>\n<p>The principle of the time value of money explains why <a href="/wiki/Interest" title="Interest">interest</a> is paid or earned: Interest, whether it is on a <a href="/wiki/Bank_deposit" class="mw-redirect" title="Bank deposit">bank deposit</a> or <a href="/wiki/Debt" title="Debt">debt</a>, compensates the depositor or lender for the time value of money.</p>\n<p>It also underlies <a href="/wiki/Investment" title="Investment">investment</a>. <a href="/wiki/Investor" title="Investor">Investors</a> are willing to forgo spending their money now if they expect a favorable <a href="/wiki/Rate_of_return" title="Rate of return">return</a> on their investment in the future.</p>\n<p></p>\n<div id="toc" class="toc">\n<div class="toctitle">\n<h2>Contents</h2>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="#History"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">History</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="#Calculations"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Calculations</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-3"><a href="#Formula"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">Formula</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-4"><a href="#Future_value_of_a_present_sum"><span class="tocnumber">3.1</span> <span class="toctext">Future value of a present sum</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-5"><a href="#Present_value_of_a_future_sum"><span class="tocnumber">3.2</span> <span class="toctext">Present value of a future sum</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-6"><a href="#Present_value_of_an_annuity_for_n_payment_periods"><span class="tocnumber">3.3</span> <span class="toctext">Present value of an annuity for n payment periods</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-7"><a href="#Present_value_of_a_growing_annuity"><span class="tocnumber">3.4</span> <span class="toctext">Present value of a growing annuity</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-8"><a href="#Present_value_of_a_perpetuity"><span class="tocnumber">3.5</span> <span class="toctext">Present value of a perpetuity</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-9"><a href="#Present_value_of_a_growing_perpetuity"><span class="tocnumber">3.6</span> <span class="toctext">Present value of a growing perpetuity</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-10"><a href="#Future_value_of_an_annuity"><span class="tocnumber">3.7</span> <span class="toctext">Future value of an annuity</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-11"><a href="#Future_value_of_a_growing_annuity"><span class="tocnumber">3.8</span> <span class="toctext">Future value of a growing annuity</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-12"><a href="#Formula_table"><span class="tocnumber">3.9</span> <span class="toctext">Formula table</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-13"><a href="#Derivations"><span class="tocnumber">4</span> <span class="toctext">Derivations</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-14"><a href="#Annuity_derivation"><span class="tocnumber">4.1</span> <span class="toctext">Annuity derivation</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-15"><a href="#Perpetuity_derivation"><span class="tocnumber">4.2</span> <span class="toctext">Perpetuity derivation</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-16"><a href="#Examples"><span class="tocnumber">5</span> <span class="toctext">Examples</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-17"><a href="#Example_1:_Present_value"><span class="tocnumber">5.1</span> <span class="toctext">Example 1: Present value</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-18"><a href="#Example_2:_Present_value_of_an_annuity.E2.80.94solving_for_the_payment_amount"><span class="tocnumber">5.2</span> <span class="toctext">Example 2: Present value of an annuity\xe2\x80\x94solving for the payment amount</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-3 tocsection-19"><a href="#An_approximate_solution"><span class="tocnumber">5.2.1</span> <span class="toctext">An approximate solution</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-20"><a href="#Example_3:_Solving_for_the_period_needed_to_double_money"><span class="tocnumber">5.3</span> <span class="toctext">Example 3: Solving for the period needed to double money</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-21"><a href="#Example_4:_What_return_is_needed_to_double_money.3F"><span class="tocnumber">5.4</span> <span class="toctext">Example 4: What return is needed to double money?</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-22"><a href="#Example_5:_Calculate_the_value_of_a_regular_savings_deposit_in_the_future."><span class="tocnumber">5.5</span> <span class="toctext">Example 5: Calculate the value of a regular savings deposit in the future.</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-23"><a href="#Example_6:_Price.2Fearnings_.28P.2FE.29_ratio"><span class="tocnumber">5.6</span> <span class="toctext">Example 6: Price/earnings (P/E) ratio</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-24"><a href="#Continuous_compounding"><span class="tocnumber">6</span> <span class="toctext">Continuous compounding</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-25"><a href="#Examples_2"><span class="tocnumber">6.1</span> <span class="toctext">Examples</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-26"><a href="#Differential_equations"><span class="tocnumber">7</span> <span class="toctext">Differential equations</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-27"><a href="#See_also"><span class="tocnumber">8</span> <span class="toctext">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-28"><a href="#Notes"><span class="tocnumber">9</span> <span class="toctext">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-29"><a href="#References"><span class="tocnumber">10</span> <span class="toctext">References</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-30"><a href="#External_links"><span class="tocnumber">11</span> <span class="toctext">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<p></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="History">History</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: History">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The notion dates back at least to <a href="/wiki/Mart%C3%ADn_de_Azpilcueta" title="Mart\xc3\xadn de Azpilcueta">Mart\xc3\xadn de Azpilcueta</a> (1491\xe2\x80\x931586) of the <a href="/wiki/School_of_Salamanca" title="School of Salamanca">School of Salamanca</a>.</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Calculations">Calculations</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Calculations">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Time value of money problems involve the net value of cash flows at different points in time.</p>\n<p>In a typical case, the variables might be: a balance (the real or nominal value of a debt or a financial asset in terms of monetary units), a periodic rate of interest, the number of periods, and a series of cash flows. (In the case of a debt, cash flows are payments against principal and interest; in the case of a financial asset, these are contributions to or withdrawals from the balance.) More generally, the cash flows may not be periodic but may be specified individually. Any of the variables may be the independent variable (the sought-for answer) in a given problem. For example, one may know that: the interest is 0.5% per period (per month, say); the number of periods is 60 (months); the initial balance (of the debt, in this case) is 25,000 units; and the final balance is 0 units. The unknown variable may be the monthly payment that the borrower must pay.</p>\n<p>For example, \xc2\xa3100 invested for one year, earning 5% interest, will be worth \xc2\xa3105 after one year; therefore, \xc2\xa3100 paid now <i>and</i> \xc2\xa3105 paid exactly one year later <i>both</i> have the same value to a recipient who expects 5% interest assuming that inflation would be zero percent. That is, \xc2\xa3100 invested for one year at 5% interest has a <i>future value</i> of \xc2\xa3105 under the assumption that inflation would be zero percent.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">[1]</a></sup></p>\n<p>This principle allows for the valuation of a likely stream of income in the future, in such a way that annual incomes are <a href="/wiki/Discounting" title="Discounting">discounted</a> and then added together, thus providing a lump-sum "present value" of the entire income stream; all of the standard calculations for time value of money derive from the most basic algebraic expression for the <a href="/wiki/Present_value" title="Present value">present value</a> of a future sum, "discounted" to the present by an amount equal to the time value of money. For example, the future value sum <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle FV}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0ae86fb323cabed7594650e78bdcbba3f88d0d66" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:3.549ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="FV" /></span> to be received in one year is discounted at the rate of interest <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>r</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle r}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0d1ecb613aa2984f0576f70f86650b7c2a132538" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.059ex; height:1.676ex;" alt="r" /></span> to give the present value sum <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle PV}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/8b6ee9fce2e1b90f60d71f454bbfcee9ea3bf0d5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:3.554ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="PV" /></span>:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>F</mi>\n              <mi>V</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>r</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle PV={\\frac {FV}{(1+r)}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7bb06c0dac39d1c15a80aee67f828fb0d90a5bd9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:14.412ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="PV = \\frac{FV}{(1+r)}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Some standard calculations based on the time value of money are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><b><a href="/wiki/Present_value" title="Present value">Present value</a></b>: The current worth of a future sum of money or stream of <a href="/wiki/Cash_flows" class="mw-redirect" title="Cash flows">cash flows</a>, given a specified <a href="/wiki/Rate_of_return" title="Rate of return">rate of return</a>. Future cash flows are "discounted" at the <i>discount&#160;rate;</i> the higher the discount rate, the lower the present value of the future cash flows. Determining the appropriate discount rate is the key to valuing future cash flows properly, whether they be earnings or obligations.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup></li>\n<li><b>Present value of an <a href="/wiki/Annuity_(finance_theory)" class="mw-redirect" title="Annuity (finance theory)">annuity</a></b>: An annuity is a series of equal payments or receipts that occur at evenly spaced intervals. Leases and rental payments are examples. The payments or receipts occur at the end of each period for an ordinary annuity while they occur at the beginning of each period for an annuity due.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup></li>\n</ul>\n<dl>\n<dd><b>Present value of a <a href="/wiki/Perpetuity" title="Perpetuity">perpetuity</a></b> is an infinite and constant stream of identical cash flows.<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup></dd>\n</dl>\n<ul>\n<li><b><a href="/wiki/Future_value" title="Future value">Future value</a></b>: The value of an asset or cash at a specified date in the future, based on the value of that asset in the present.<sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup></li>\n<li><b>Future value of an annuity (FVA)</b>: The future value of a stream of payments (annuity), assuming the payments are invested at a given rate of interest.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>There are several basic equations that represent the equalities listed above. The solutions may be found using (in most cases) the formulas, a financial calculator or a <a href="/wiki/Spreadsheet" title="Spreadsheet">spreadsheet</a>. The formulas are programmed into most financial calculators and several spreadsheet functions (such as PV, FV, RATE, NPER, and PMT).<sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup></p>\n<p>For any of the equations below, the formula may also be rearranged to determine one of the other unknowns. In the case of the standard annuity formula, however, there is no closed-form algebraic solution for the interest rate (although financial calculators and spreadsheet programs can readily determine solutions through rapid trial and error algorithms).</p>\n<p>These equations are frequently combined for particular uses. For example, <a href="/wiki/Bond_(finance)" title="Bond (finance)">bonds</a> can be readily priced using these equations. A typical coupon bond is composed of two types of payments: a stream of coupon payments similar to an annuity, and a lump-sum <a href="/wiki/Return_of_capital" title="Return of capital">return of capital</a> at the end of the bond\'s <a href="/wiki/Maturity_(finance)" title="Maturity (finance)">maturity</a>\xe2\x80\x94that is, a future payment. The two formulas can be combined to determine the present value of the bond.</p>\n<p>An important note is that the interest rate <i>i</i> is the interest rate for the relevant period. For an annuity that makes one payment per year, <i>i</i> will be the annual interest rate. For an income or payment stream with a different payment schedule, the interest rate must be converted into the relevant periodic interest rate. For example, a monthly rate for a mortgage with monthly payments requires that the interest rate be divided by 12 (see the example below). See <a href="/wiki/Compound_interest" title="Compound interest">compound interest</a> for details on converting between different periodic interest rates.</p>\n<p>The rate of return in the calculations can be either the variable solved for, or a predefined variable that measures a discount rate, interest, inflation, rate of return, cost of equity, cost of debt or any number of other analogous concepts. The choice of the appropriate rate is critical to the exercise, and the use of an incorrect discount rate will make the results meaningless.</p>\n<p>For calculations involving annuities, you must decide whether the payments are made at the end of each period (known as an ordinary annuity), or at the beginning of each period (known as an annuity due). If you are using a financial calculator or a <a href="/wiki/Spreadsheet" title="Spreadsheet">spreadsheet</a>, you can usually set it for either calculation. The following formulas are for an ordinary annuity. If you want the answer for the present value of an annuity due simply multiply the PV of an ordinary annuity by (1 + <i>i</i>).</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Formula">Formula</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Formula">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The following formula use these common variables:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><i>PV</i> is the value at time=0 (present value)</li>\n<li><i>FV</i> is the value at time=n (future value)</li>\n<li><i>A</i> is the value of the individual payments in each compounding period</li>\n<li><i>n</i> is the number of periods (not necessarily an integer)</li>\n<li><i>i</i> is the <a href="/wiki/Interest_rate" title="Interest rate">interest rate</a> at which the amount compounds each period</li>\n<li><i>g</i> is the growing rate of payments over each time period</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Future_value_of_a_present_sum">Future value of a present sum</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Future value of a present sum">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The <a href="/wiki/Future_value" title="Future value">future value</a> (FV) formula is similar and uses the same variables.</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle FV\\ =\\ PV\\cdot (1+i)^{n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d85e77797915e386a330e3b2143ef47426dd477b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:20.955ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="  FV   \\ = \\  PV \\cdot (1+i)^n " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Present_value_of_a_future_sum">Present value of a future sum</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Present value of a future sum">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The present value formula is the core formula for the time value of money; each of the other formulae is derived from this formula. For example, the annuity formula is the sum of a series of present value calculations.</p>\n<p>The <a href="/wiki/Present_value" title="Present value">present value</a> (PV) formula has four variables, each of which can be solved for:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>F</mi>\n              <mi>V</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle PV\\ =\\ {\\frac {FV}{(1+i)^{n}}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/47e4bca443c4973f64e3e06f238792fefd224152" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:16.553ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="  PV \\ = \\ \\frac{FV}{(1+i)^n} " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>The cumulative <a href="/wiki/Present_value" title="Present value">present value</a> of future cash flows can be calculated by summing the contributions of <i>FV<sub>t</sub></i>, the value of cash flow at time <i>t</i></p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <munderover>\n          <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \xe2\x88\x91 --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>t</mi>\n            <mo>=</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </munderover>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>F</mi>\n              <msub>\n                <mi>V</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>t</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msub>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>t</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle PV\\ =\\ \\sum _{t=1}^{n}{\\frac {FV_{t}}{(1+i)^{t}}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/da319333bc4b1d22fd214a1bd03ee8ddfca5ce3d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -3.005ex; width:20.3ex; height:7.009ex;" alt="PV\\ =\\ \\sum _{{t=1}}^{{n}}{\\frac  {FV_{{t}}}{(1+i)^{t}}}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Note that this series can be summed for a given value of <i>n</i>, or when <i>n</i> is \xe2\x88\x9e.<sup id="cite_ref-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup> This is a very general formula, which leads to several important special cases given below.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Present_value_of_an_annuity_for_n_payment_periods">Present value of an annuity for n payment periods</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Present value of an annuity for n payment periods">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In this case the cash flow values remain the same throughout the n periods. The present value of an <a href="/wiki/Annuity_(finance_theory)" class="mw-redirect" title="Annuity (finance theory)">annuity</a> (PVA) formula has four variables, each of which can be solved for:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>A</mi>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>[</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n                <msup>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mo>(</mo>\n                    <mn>1</mn>\n                    <mo>+</mo>\n                    <mi>i</mi>\n                    <mo>)</mo>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>n</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>]</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle PV(A)\\,=\\,{\\frac {A}{i}}\\cdot \\left[{1-{\\frac {1}{\\left(1+i\\right)^{n}}}}\\right]}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/219c8546045563d07ca0789d7f56aab396f97f09" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.838ex; width:30.528ex; height:6.509ex;" alt="PV(A) \\,=\\,\\frac{A}{i} \\cdot \\left[ {1-\\frac{1}{\\left(1+i\\right)^n}} \\right] " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>To get the PV of an <a href="/wiki/Annuity_(finance_theory)#Annuity-due" class="mw-redirect" title="Annuity (finance theory)">annuity due</a>, multiply the above equation by (1 + <i>i</i>).</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Present_value_of_a_growing_annuity">Present value of a growing annuity</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Present value of a growing annuity">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In this case each cash flow grows by a factor of (1+g). Similar to the formula for an annuity, the present value of a growing annuity (PVGA) uses the same variables with the addition of <i>g</i> as the rate of growth of the annuity (A is the annuity payment in the first period). This is a calculation that is rarely provided for on financial calculators.</p>\n<p><b>Where i \xe2\x89\xa0 g&#160;:</b></p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>A</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mi>g</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>[</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>(</mo>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mfrac>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mn>1</mn>\n                    <mo>+</mo>\n                    <mi>g</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mn>1</mn>\n                    <mo>+</mo>\n                    <mi>i</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mfrac>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi>n</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n          <mo>]</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle PV\\,=\\,{A \\over (i-g)}\\left[1-\\left({1+g \\over 1+i}\\right)^{n}\\right]}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/324bde5f479c2b441901188d72f219d7484b464a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:32.434ex; height:6.343ex;" alt="PV\\,=\\,{A \\over (i-g)}\\left[ 1- \\left({1+g \\over 1+i}\\right)^n \\right] " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p><b>Where i = g&#160;:</b></p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>A</mi>\n              <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n              <mi>n</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle PV\\,=\\,{A\\times n \\over 1+i}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a425fa01d3e96a5fa43143bd05ba1c456562c4c4" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.005ex; width:14.282ex; height:5.509ex;" alt="PV\\,=\\,{A \\times n \\over 1+i} " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>To get the PV of a growing <a href="/wiki/Annuity_(finance_theory)#Annuity-due" class="mw-redirect" title="Annuity (finance theory)">annuity due</a>, multiply the above equation by (1 + <i>i</i>).</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Present_value_of_a_perpetuity">Present value of a perpetuity</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Present value of a perpetuity">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>A perpetuity is payments of a set amount of money that occur on a routine basis and continues forever. When <i>n</i> \xe2\x86\x92 \xe2\x88\x9e, the <i>PV</i> of a perpetuity (a perpetual annuity) formula becomes simple division.</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>A</mi>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle PV(P)\\ =\\ {A \\over i}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/73866691a305aa75ccb14ab964a634e40be2a201" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.838ex; width:14ex; height:5.343ex;" alt="PV(P) \\ = \\ { A \\over i } " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Present Value of Int Factor Annuity</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo>/</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>n</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n            <mi>t</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle A=P(1+r/n)^{nt}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d61fc6b196d4861a71e2432b4f46e748fecc386f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:17.936ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="A=P(1+r/n)^{nt}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Example:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd>Investment <i>P</i> = $1000</dd>\n<dd>Interest <i>i</i> = 6.90% Compounded Qtrly (4 Times in Year)</dd>\n<dd>Tenure Years <i>n</i> = 5</dd>\n</dl>\n<p><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>1000</mn>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mn>0.069</mn>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo>/</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mn>5</mn>\n              <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n              <mi>y</mi>\n              <mi>r</mi>\n              <mi>s</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n            <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n            <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n            <mn>4</mn>\n            <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi>q</mi>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mi>r</mi>\n              <mi>s</mi>\n              <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mi>n</mi>\n              <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n              <mi>a</mi>\n              <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n              <mi>y</mi>\n              <mi>e</mi>\n              <mi>a</mi>\n              <mi>r</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>1000</mn>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mn>0.069</mn>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo>/</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>20</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x2248;<!-- \xe2\x89\x88 --></mo>\n        <mn>1407.84</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle =1000\\times (1+0.069/4)^{({5\\ yrs}\\ \\times \\ 4\\ {qtrs\\ in\\ a\\ year})}=1000\\times (1+0.069/4)^{20}\\approx 1407.84}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f339702e738cba09678935aa3e032c23d3bf4cff" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:79.898ex; height:3.343ex;" alt="&#10;= 1000 \\times (1+0.069/4)^{({5\\ yrs}\\ \\times\\ 4\\ {qtrs\\ in\\ a\\ year} )}&#10;= 1000 \\times (1+0.069/4)^{20}&#10;\\approx 1407.84&#10;" /></span></p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Present_value_of_a_growing_perpetuity">Present value of a growing perpetuity</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Present value of a growing perpetuity">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>When the perpetual annuity payment grows at a fixed rate (g) the value is theoretically determined according to the following formula. In practice, there are few securities with precise characteristics, and the application of this valuation approach is subject to various qualifications and modifications. Most importantly, it is rare to find a growing perpetual annuity with fixed rates of growth and true perpetual cash flow generation. Despite these qualifications, the general approach may be used in valuations of real estate, equities, and other assets.</p>\n<p>This is the well known <a href="/wiki/Gordon_model" class="mw-redirect" title="Gordon model">Gordon Growth model</a> used for <a href="/wiki/Stock_valuation" title="Stock valuation">stock valuation</a>.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Future_value_of_an_annuity">Future value of an annuity</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Future value of an annuity">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The future value of an annuity (FVA) formula has four variables, each of which can be solved for:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <msup>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>(</mo>\n                  <mn>1</mn>\n                  <mo>+</mo>\n                  <mi>i</mi>\n                  <mo>)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle FV(A)\\,=\\,A\\cdot {\\frac {\\left(1+i\\right)^{n}-1}{i}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/794f7f6510f896767a34e5e6dac899b027988317" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.838ex; width:27.212ex; height:5.843ex;" alt="FV(A) \\,=\\,A\\cdot\\frac{\\left(1+i\\right)^n-1}{i}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>To get the FV of an annuity due, multiply the above equation by (1 + i).</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Future_value_of_a_growing_annuity">Future value of a growing annuity</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Future value of a growing annuity">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The future value of a growing annuity (FVA) formula has five variables, each of which can be solved for:</p>\n<p><b>Where i \xe2\x89\xa0 g&#160;:</b></p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <msup>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>(</mo>\n                  <mn>1</mn>\n                  <mo>+</mo>\n                  <mi>i</mi>\n                  <mo>)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <msup>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>(</mo>\n                  <mn>1</mn>\n                  <mo>+</mo>\n                  <mi>g</mi>\n                  <mo>)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mi>g</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle FV(A)\\,=\\,A\\cdot {\\frac {\\left(1+i\\right)^{n}-\\left(1+g\\right)^{n}}{i-g}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/40c4f7f3d709f0429de9e596ff5c546775d64a73" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:34.245ex; height:6.343ex;" alt="FV(A) \\,=\\,A\\cdot\\frac{\\left(1+i\\right)^n-\\left(1+g\\right)^n}{i-g}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p><b>Where i = g&#160;:</b></p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>n</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle FV(A)\\,=\\,A\\cdot n(1+i)^{n-1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3e71306a7ee7898918a69dcc7f8b5fdf7e6bd350" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:25.872ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="FV(A) \\,=\\,A\\cdot n(1+i)^{n-1}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Formula_table">Formula table</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Formula table">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The following table summarizes the different formulas commonly used in calculating the time value of money.<sup id="cite_ref-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup> These values are often displayed in tables where the interest rate and time are specified.</p>\n<table class="wikitable">\n<tr>\n<th>Find</th>\n<th>Given</th>\n<th>Formula</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Future value (F)</td>\n<td>Present value (P)</td>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle F=P\\cdot (1+i)^{n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ff91ef9268f6bc2d218596fae80838342447a9d7" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:16.198ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="F=P\\cdot (1+i)^n" /></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Present value (P)</td>\n<td>Future value (F)</td>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle P=F\\cdot (1+i)^{-n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d83ff324c0c053bec4e8f07061d8226899b7f45c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:17.484ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="P=F\\cdot (1+i)^{-n}" /></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Repeating payment (A)</td>\n<td>Future value (F)</td>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle A=F\\cdot {\\frac {i}{(1+i)^{n}-1}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/11996c510658b1af798dd7691697ecab2af890ef" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:21.056ex; height:6.009ex;" alt="A=F\\cdot \\frac{i}{(1+i)^n-1}" /></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Repeating payment (A)</td>\n<td>Present value (P)</td>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle A=P\\cdot {\\frac {i(1+i)^{n}}{(1+i)^{n}-1}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3e8312934bb3ae145717b7fb153af248c8778df0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:21.061ex; height:6.509ex;" alt="A=P\\cdot \\frac{i(1+i)^n}{(1+i)^n-1}" /></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Future value (F)</td>\n<td>Repeating payment (A)</td>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle F=A\\cdot {\\frac {(1+i)^{n}-1}{i}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2a257dd6d1aa38923ff6c0f0be42feb5e6ffa988" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.838ex; width:21.056ex; height:5.676ex;" alt="F=A\\cdot \\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i}" /></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Present value (P)</td>\n<td>Repeating payment (A)</td>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle P=A\\cdot {\\frac {(1+i)^{n}-1}{i(1+i)^{n}}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/33ca240e2a5734f23c42e13f786dca45584de864" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:21.061ex; height:6.509ex;" alt="P=A\\cdot \\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i(1+i)^n}" /></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Future value (F)</td>\n<td>Gradient payment (G)</td>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>G</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mi>n</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </msup>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle F=G\\cdot {\\frac {(1+i)^{n}-in-1}{i^{2}}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/5667ef393c015e795b96e3365df76b9952b4d8f4" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.171ex; width:26.208ex; height:6.009ex;" alt="F=G\\cdot \\frac{(1+i)^n-in-1}{i^2}" /></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Present value (P)</td>\n<td>Gradient payment (G)</td>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>G</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mi>n</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>i</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mn>2</mn>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle P=G\\cdot {\\frac {(1+i)^{n}-in-1}{i^{2}(1+i)^{n}}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c9ec91ce2e474567809912daccdfbae738a03cce" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:26.213ex; height:6.509ex;" alt="P=G\\cdot \\frac{(1+i)^n-in-1}{i^2(1+i)^n}" /></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Fixed payment (A)</td>\n<td>Gradient payment (G)</td>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>G</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>[</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mi>n</mi>\n              <mrow>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mi>i</mi>\n                <msup>\n                  <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>n</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n                <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n              </mrow>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>]</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle A=G\\cdot \\left[{\\frac {1}{i}}-{\\frac {n}{(1+i)^{n}-1}}\\right]}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/faf7c462c8b5603d2c602b60fe4300c298fe617d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:28.478ex; height:6.343ex;" alt="A=G\\cdot \\left[\\frac{1}{i}-\\frac{n}{(1+i)^n-1}\\right]" /></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Future value (F)</td>\n<td>Exponentially increasing payment (D)\n<p>Increasing percentage (g)</p>\n</td>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>g</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>g</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle F=D\\cdot {\\frac {(1+g)^{n}-(1+i)^{n}}{g-i}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f49e4f268eb4477d2da3da3d866b489b54f18363" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:28.27ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="F=D\\cdot \\frac{(1+g)^n-(1+i)^n}{g-i}" /></span> &#160; (for i \xe2\x89\xa0 g)\n<p><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>n</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>g</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle F=D\\cdot {\\frac {n(1+i)^{n}}{1+g}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/02b630a0de916cd64f0c489c2f861fd5a3ca2e8e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:18.618ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="F=D\\cdot \\frac{n(1+i)^n}{1+g}" /></span> &#160; (for i = g)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Present value (P)</td>\n<td>Exponentially increasing payment (D)\n<p>Increasing percentage (g)</p>\n</td>\n<td><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <msup>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>(</mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mfrac>\n                      <mrow>\n                        <mn>1</mn>\n                        <mo>+</mo>\n                        <mi>g</mi>\n                      </mrow>\n                      <mrow>\n                        <mn>1</mn>\n                        <mo>+</mo>\n                        <mi>i</mi>\n                      </mrow>\n                    </mfrac>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mo>)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>g</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle P=D\\cdot {\\frac {\\left({1+g \\over 1+i}\\right)^{n}-1}{g-i}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/053a1c3764f753013408d7fd3274d331ae93fd2c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:21.119ex; height:8.176ex;" alt="P=D\\cdot \\frac{\\left({1+g \\over 1+i}\\right)^n-1}{g-i}" /></span> &#160; (for i \xe2\x89\xa0 g)\n<p><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>D</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>n</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>g</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle P=D\\cdot {\\frac {n}{1+g}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/8e3ad4d0613475bc2dc6d52739c2e0bd5edb2451" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:14.475ex; height:5.176ex;" alt="P=D\\cdot \\frac{n}{1+g}" /></span> &#160; (for i = g)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>Notes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><i>A</i> is a fixed payment amount, every period</li>\n<li><i>G</i> is a steadily increasing payment amount, that starts at <i>G</i> and increases by <i>G</i> for each subsequent period.</li>\n<li><i>D</i> is an exponentially or geometrically increasing payment amount, that starts at <i>D</i> and increases by a factor of (1+<i>g</i>) each subsequent period.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Derivations">Derivations</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Derivations">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Annuity_derivation">Annuity derivation</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Annuity derivation">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The formula for the present value of a regular stream of future payments (an annuity) is derived from a sum of the formula for future value of a single future payment, as below, where <i>C</i> is the payment amount and <i>n</i> the period.</p>\n<p>A single payment C at future time <i>m</i> has the following future value at future time <i>n</i>:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>C</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle FV\\ =C(1+i)^{n-m}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/11cd95bfbd867d523f6ee1376e6e413de02e0b9e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:19.644ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="FV \\ = C(1+i)^{n-m}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Summing over all payments from time 1 to time n, then reversing t</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <munderover>\n          <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \xe2\x88\x91 --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>m</mi>\n            <mo>=</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </munderover>\n        <mi>C</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <munderover>\n          <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \xe2\x88\x91 --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n            <mo>=</mo>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </munderover>\n        <mi>C</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>k</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle FVA\\ =\\sum _{m=1}^{n}C(1+i)^{n-m}\\ =\\sum _{k=0}^{n-1}C(1+i)^{k}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/6f67d4ed143acae7c293b0953c008acef4a38daa" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -3.171ex; width:42.332ex; height:7.509ex;" alt="FVA \\ = \\sum_{m=1}^n C(1+i)^{n-m} \\ = \\sum_{k=0}^{n-1} C(1+i)^k" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Note that this is a <a href="/wiki/Geometric_series" title="Geometric series">geometric series</a>, with the initial value being <i>a</i> = <i>C</i>, the multiplicative factor being 1 + <i>i</i>, with <i>n</i> terms. Applying the formula for geometric series, we get</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>C</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>C</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle FVA\\ ={\\frac {C(1-(1+i)^{n})}{1-(1+i)}}\\ ={\\frac {C(1-(1+i)^{n})}{-i}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/dadc536785b3176de915b6e67a8ad2af118e5f3f" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:45.401ex; height:6.509ex;" alt="FVA \\ = \\frac{ C ( 1 - (1+i)^n )}{1 - (1+i)} \\ = \\frac{ C ( 1 - (1+i)^n )}{-i} " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>The present value of the annuity (PVA) is obtained by simply dividing by <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle (1+i)^{n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2e84b640a1c3db2fa63fae081d8df136304bcad5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:7.893ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="(1+i)^n" /></span>:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>F</mi>\n              <mi>V</mi>\n              <mi>A</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>C</mi>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mrow>\n                <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mi>i</mi>\n                <msup>\n                  <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                  <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                    <mi>n</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </msup>\n              </mrow>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle PVA\\ ={\\frac {FVA}{(1+i)^{n}}}={\\frac {C}{i}}\\left(1-{\\frac {1}{(1+i)^{n}}}\\right)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9ee7e7893d4d62a13ba189885c4459af8a95eb7b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:40.029ex; height:6.343ex;" alt="PVA \\ = \\frac{FVA}{(1+i)^n} = \\frac{C}{i} \\left( 1 - \\frac{1}{(1+i)^n} \\right)" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Another simple and intuitive way to derive the future value of an annuity is to consider an endowment, whose interest is paid as the annuity, and whose principal remains constant. The principal of this hypothetical endowment can be computed as that whose interest equals the annuity payment amount:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mtext>Principal</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>C</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\text{Principal}}\\times i=C}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d4f01d7a9974a033703daa715ecc7c3dd27ce38d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:17.858ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="\\text{Principal} \\times i = C" /></span></dd>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mtext>Principal</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>C</mi>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo>/</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mi>g</mi>\n          <mi>o</mi>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mi>l</mi>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\text{Principal}}=C/i+{goal}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/eaa80df9b918a39adff65650e3df8a64ffd7745c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:23.24ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\text{Principal} = C / i + {goal} " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Note that no money enters or leaves the combined system of endowment principal + accumulated annuity payments, and thus the future value of this system can be computed simply via the future value formula:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle FV=PV(1+i)^{n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e1c186efa9bbe7d655f330233c3d8621eddf8b92" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:18.104ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="FV = PV(1+i)^n" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Initially, before any payments, the present value of the system is just the endowment principal (<span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>C</mi>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo>/</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle PV=C/i}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/37ab58730b195ea1eb2e4355fb43dd56206f02cc" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:10.425ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="PV = C/i" /></span>). At the end, the future value is the endowment principal (which is the same) plus the future value of the total annuity payments (<span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>C</mi>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo>/</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle FV=C/i+FVA}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9945981f683be18cc3d8f2778d97a4b4e9134ce3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:18.574ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="FV = C/i + FVA" /></span>). Plugging this back into the equation:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>C</mi>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>C</mi>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\frac {C}{i}}+FVA={\\frac {C}{i}}(1+i)^{n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/87acd61a08b808599e49ab481ba1b33b072a8ce9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.838ex; width:24.381ex; height:5.343ex;" alt="\\frac{C}{i} + FVA = \\frac{C}{i} (1+i)^n" /></span></dd>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>C</mi>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>[</mo>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mo>)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi>n</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </msup>\n          <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mo>]</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle FVA={\\frac {C}{i}}\\left[\\left(1+i\\right)^{n}-1\\right]}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/dff9881727f970aa1334efd5941375e4dd1cd9e5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.838ex; width:24.642ex; height:5.343ex;" alt="FVA = \\frac{C}{i} \\left[ \\left(1+i \\right)^n - 1 \\right]" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Perpetuity_derivation">Perpetuity derivation</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Perpetuity derivation">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Without showing the formal derivation here, the perpetuity formula is derived from the annuity formula. Specifically, the term:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                  <mn>1</mn>\n                  <mo>+</mo>\n                  <mi>i</mi>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <mi>n</mi>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msup>\n                </mrow>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\left({1-{1 \\over {(1+i)^{n}}}}\\right)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/8c2e6dfd11d1ebb57537876d695698d09fe23a19" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:16.195ex; height:6.343ex;" alt=" \\left({1 - {1 \\over { (1+i)^n } }}\\right) " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>can be seen to approach the value of 1 as <i>n</i> grows larger. At infinity, it is equal to 1, leaving <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>C</mi>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {C \\over i}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d52e18fce225380bc7e654599f5e21d4b312e431" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.838ex; width:2.613ex; height:5.343ex;" alt=" {C \\over i} " /></span> as the only term remaining.</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Examples">Examples</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: Examples">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Example_1:_Present_value">Example 1: Present value</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: Example 1: Present value">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>One hundred euros to be paid 1 year from now, where the expected rate of return is 5% per year, is worth in today\'s money:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo>/</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>100</mn>\n            <mn>1.05</mn>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>95.24</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle P=F\\times (P/F)=F\\times {1 \\over (1+i)^{n}}={\\frac {100}{1.05}}=95.24}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/de8274ef00d39a7487efd11149b1a3f26a71cb27" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:48.996ex; height:6.009ex;" alt="P=F\\times (P/F)=F\\times {1 \\over (1+i)^{n}}={\\frac  {100}{1.05}}=95.24" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>So the present value of \xe2\x82\xac100 one year from now at 5% is \xe2\x82\xac95.24.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Example_2:_Present_value_of_an_annuity.E2.80.94solving_for_the_payment_amount">Example 2: Present value of an annuity\xe2\x80\x94solving for the payment amount</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18" title="Edit section: Example 2: Present value of an annuity\xe2\x80\x94solving for the payment amount">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Consider a 10-year mortgage where the principal amount <i>P</i> is $200,000 and the annual interest rate is 6%.</p>\n<p>The number of monthly payments is</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>n</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>10</mn>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">y</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mn>12</mn>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">h</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi>\n            <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">p</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi>\n            <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">y</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>120</mn>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">h</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle n=10{\\rm {\\ years}}\\times 12{\\rm {\\ months\\ per\\ year}}=120{\\rm {\\ months}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/877b829535c6847fbcc527bb50780f5963ade0ad" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:49.668ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=" n = 10 {\\rm \\ years} \\times 12 {\\rm \\ months \\ per \\ year} = 120 {\\rm \\ months}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>and the monthly interest rate is</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>6</mn>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x0025;<!-- % --></mi>\n                  <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">p</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi>\n                  <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">y</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </mrow>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>12</mn>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">h</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi>\n                  <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">p</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi>\n                  <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">y</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi>\n                  <mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </mrow>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>0.5</mn>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x0025;<!-- % --></mi>\n            <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">p</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi>\n            <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">h</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle i={6{\\rm {\\%\\ per\\ year}} \\over 12{\\rm {\\ months\\ per\\ year}}}=0.5{\\rm {\\%\\ per\\ month}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/bdfcbbe98f9349e56805a4fc9fc44f89d0730aaf" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:43.184ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=" i = { 6 {\\rm \\% \\ per \\ year} \\over 12 {\\rm \\ months \\ per \\ year} } =  0.5 {\\rm \\% \\ per \\ month} " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>The <a href="/wiki/Annuity_(finance_theory)#Proof" class="mw-redirect" title="Annuity (finance theory)">annuity formula</a> for (<i>A</i>/<i>P</i>) calculates the monthly payment:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mi>A</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>/</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mi>P</mi>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x0024;<!-- $ --></mi>\n        <mn>200</mn>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mn>000</mn>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>0.005</mn>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1.005</mn>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mn>120</mn>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1.005</mn>\n              <msup>\n                <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mn>120</mn>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle A\\ =\\ P\\times \\left(A/P\\right)\\ =\\ P\\times {i(1+i)^{n} \\over (1+i)^{n}-1}\\ =\\ \\$200,000\\times {0.005(1.005)^{120} \\over (1.005)^{120}-1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ffee2db7cbb0453a4c0264fc0ec907b598b10157" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:71.62ex; height:6.676ex;" alt=" A \\ = \\ P \\times \\left( A / P  \\right) \\ = \\ P \\times {  i (1+i)^n \\over (1+i)^n - 1   }&#10;\\ = \\ \\$200,000 \\times { 0.005(1.005)^{120}  \\over (1.005)^{120} - 1 } " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<dl>\n<dd>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo>&#x2248;<!-- \xe2\x89\x88 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x0024;<!-- $ --></mi>\n        <mn>200</mn>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mn>000</mn>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mn>0.01110205</mn>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>&#x2248;<!-- \xe2\x89\x88 --></mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x0024;<!-- $ --></mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mn>220.41</mn>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">p</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">r</mi>\n            <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">t</mi>\n            <mi mathvariant="normal">h</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\approx \\$200,000\\times 0.01110205\\ \\approx \\ \\$2,220.41{\\rm {\\ per\\ month}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7745ac949743350e4409d621a29de445f870f624" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:51.035ex; height:2.676ex;" alt="  \\approx \\$200,000 \\times 0.01110205 \\ \\approx \\ \\$2,220.41 {\\rm \\ per \\ month} " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<p>This is considering an interest rate compounding monthly. If the interest were only to compound yearly at 6%, the monthly payment would be significantly different.</p>\n<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="An_approximate_solution">An approximate solution</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=19" title="Edit section: An approximate solution">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>\n<p>For those who only want a rough idea of the mortgage payment there is a much less intimidating approximate formula <a href="/wiki/Present_value#An_approximation_for_annuity_and_loan_calculations" title="Present value">here</a>. For the numbers given above we simply compute an approximate annual repayment of 200,000*(1/n + (2/3)*i) where n=10 yrs, i=0.06. So 200,000*(1/10 + (2/3)*0.06) = 200,000*(0.1+0.04) = 200,000*0.14 = $28,000 per year, roughly, via mental arithmetic alone. Note, as this is an approximation we may ignore the subtleties of monthly compounding. Now $28,000 per year is about 28,000/12 = $2,333 per month, which approximates the true answer to within about 5% but has required only mental arithmetic.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Example_3:_Solving_for_the_period_needed_to_double_money">Example 3: Solving for the period needed to double money</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=20" title="Edit section: Example 3: Solving for the period needed to double money">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Consider a deposit of \xc2\xa3100 placed at 10% (annual). How many years are needed for the value of the deposit to double to \xc2\xa3200?</p>\n<p>Using the algrebraic identity that if:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>b</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>y</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle x\\ =\\ b^{y}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/906ebb71df3eded1af1d70b8b739e01e520c0286" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:7.675ex; height:2.343ex;" alt=" x \\ = \\ b^y " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>then</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>y</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>log</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \xe2\x81\xa1 --></mo>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mi>x</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>log</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \xe2\x81\xa1 --></mo>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mi>b</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle y\\ =\\ {\\log(x) \\over \\log(b)}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7d487dd7aa7f274136f07917e8c96cfc2aea1b1b" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:12.446ex; height:6.509ex;" alt=" y \\ = \\ {\\log (x) \\over \\log(b)} " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>The present value formula can be rearranged such that:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>y</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>log</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \xe2\x81\xa1 --></mo>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mfrac>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mi>F</mi>\n                    <mi>V</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                  <mrow>\n                    <mi>P</mi>\n                    <mi>V</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mfrac>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>log</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \xe2\x81\xa1 --></mo>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>log</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \xe2\x81\xa1 --></mo>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mfrac>\n                  <mn>200</mn>\n                  <mn>100</mn>\n                </mfrac>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>log</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \xe2\x81\xa1 --></mo>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1.10</mn>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mn>7.27</mn>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mi>y</mi>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mi>r</mi>\n          <mi>s</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle y\\ =\\ {\\log({FV \\over PV}) \\over \\log(1+i)}\\ =\\ {\\log({200 \\over 100}) \\over \\log(1.10)}\\ =\\ 7.27{(years)}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/eb0fed1e10ee3a7a994ce0d850d629004eaa0bb2" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:45.994ex; height:7.343ex;" alt=" y \\ = \\ {\\log ({FV \\over PV}) \\over \\log (1+i)} \\ = \\  {\\log ({200 \\over 100}) \\over \\log (1.10)} \\ =\\ 7.27   {(years)} " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>This same method can be used to determine the length of time needed to increase a deposit to any particular sum, as long as the interest rate is known. For the period of time needed to double an investment, the <a href="/wiki/Rule_of_72" title="Rule of 72">Rule of 72</a> is a useful short-cut that gives a reasonable approximation of the period needed.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Example_4:_What_return_is_needed_to_double_money.3F">Example 4: What return is needed to double money?</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: Example 4: What return is needed to double money?">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Similarly, the present value formula can be rearranged to determine what <a href="/wiki/Rate_of_return" title="Rate of return">rate of return</a> is needed to accumulate a given amount from an investment. For example, \xc2\xa3100 is invested today and \xc2\xa3200 return is expected in five years; what rate of return (interest rate) does this represent?</p>\n<p>The present value formula restated in terms of the interest rate is:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>(</mo>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mfrac>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mi>F</mi>\n                  <mi>V</mi>\n                </mrow>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mi>P</mi>\n                  <mi>V</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mi>n</mi>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>(</mo>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>200</mn>\n                <mn>100</mn>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mn>5</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <msup>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>0.20</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mn>0.15</mn>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mn>15</mn>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x0025;<!-- % --></mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle i\\ =\\ \\left({FV \\over PV}\\right)^{1 \\over n}-1\\ =\\ \\left({200 \\over 100}\\right)^{1 \\over 5}-1\\ =\\ 2^{0.20}-1\\ =\\ 0.15\\ =\\ 15\\%}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b769f5423833f4d5fc0bde6c8a175009fbac664e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:66.307ex; height:7.343ex;" alt=" i \\ = \\ \\left({FV \\over PV}\\right)^{1 \\over n} - 1 \\ = \\ \\left({200 \\over 100}\\right)^{1 \\over 5} - 1 \\ = \\ 2^{0.20} - 1 \\ = \\ 0.15 \\ = \\ 15\\% " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<dl>\n<dd>see also <a href="/wiki/Rule_of_72" title="Rule of 72">Rule of 72</a></dd>\n</dl>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Example_5:_Calculate_the_value_of_a_regular_savings_deposit_in_the_future.">Example 5: Calculate the value of a regular savings deposit in the future.</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: Example 5: Calculate the value of a regular savings deposit in the future.">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>To calculate the future value of a stream of savings deposit in the future requires two steps, or, alternatively, combining the two steps into one large formula. First, calculate the present value of a stream of deposits of $1,000 every year for 20 years earning 7% interest:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mfrac>\n                  <mn>1</mn>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mrow>\n                      <mo>(</mo>\n                      <mn>1</mn>\n                      <mo>+</mo>\n                      <mi>i</mi>\n                      <mo>)</mo>\n                    </mrow>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <mi>n</mi>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msup>\n                </mfrac>\n              </mrow>\n            </mrow>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mn>1000</mn>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mfrac>\n                  <mn>1</mn>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mrow>\n                      <mo>(</mo>\n                      <mn>1</mn>\n                      <mo>+</mo>\n                      <mn>.07</mn>\n                      <mo>)</mo>\n                    </mrow>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <mn>20</mn>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msup>\n                </mfrac>\n              </mrow>\n            </mrow>\n            <mn>.07</mn>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mn>1000</mn>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>0.258</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mn>.07</mn>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mn>1000</mn>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mn>10.594</mn>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>&#x2248;<!-- \xe2\x89\x88 --></mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x0024;<!-- $ --></mi>\n        <mn>10</mn>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mn>594</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle PVA\\,=\\,A\\cdot {\\frac {1-{\\frac {1}{\\left(1+i\\right)^{n}}}}{i}}\\ =\\ 1000\\cdot {\\frac {1-{\\frac {1}{\\left(1+.07\\right)^{20}}}}{.07}}\\ =\\ 1000\\cdot {1-0.258 \\over .07}\\ =\\ 1000\\times 10.594\\ \\approx \\ \\$10,594}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0e42f05206a5fc6bd078f9a7360d1842ec5b91ca" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.005ex; width:98.223ex; height:7.509ex;" alt="PVA \\,=\\,A\\cdot\\frac{1-\\frac{1}{\\left(1+i\\right)^n}}{i} \\ = \\ 1000\\cdot\\frac{1-\\frac{1}{\\left(1+.07\\right)^{20}}}{.07} \\ = \\ 1000\\cdot {1- 0.258 \\over .07} \\ = \\ 1000 \\times 10.594 \\ \\approx \\ \\$10,594" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>This does not sound like very much, but remember - this is <i>future money</i> discounted back to its value <i>today</i>; it is understandably lower. To calculate the future value (at the end of the twenty-year period):</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x0024;<!-- $ --></mi>\n        <mn>10</mn>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mn>594</mn>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mn>.07</mn>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mn>20</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>&#x2248;<!-- \xe2\x89\x88 --></mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x0024;<!-- $ --></mi>\n        <mn>10</mn>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mn>594</mn>\n        <mo>&#x00D7;<!-- \xc3\x97 --></mo>\n        <mn>3.87</mn>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x0024;<!-- $ --></mi>\n        <mn>40</mn>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mn>995</mn>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle FV\\ =\\ PV(1+i)^{n}\\ =\\$10,594\\times (1+.07)^{20}\\ \\approx \\$10,594\\times 3.87\\ =\\$40,995}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/8b9d031dc767b9459121c12cdbe4217c9faf2495" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:75.205ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="  FV   \\ = \\  PV  (1+i)^n \\ = \\$ 10,594 \\times (1+.07)^{20} \\ \\approx \\$ 10,594 \\times 3.87 \\ = \\$40,995 " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>These steps can be combined into a single formula:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>F</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mfrac>\n                  <mn>1</mn>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mrow>\n                      <mo>(</mo>\n                      <mn>1</mn>\n                      <mo>+</mo>\n                      <mi>i</mi>\n                      <mo>)</mo>\n                    </mrow>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <mi>n</mi>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msup>\n                </mfrac>\n              </mrow>\n            </mrow>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <msup>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <msup>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mo>(</mo>\n                  <mn>1</mn>\n                  <mo>+</mo>\n                  <mi>i</mi>\n                  <mo>)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle FV\\,=\\,A\\cdot {\\frac {1-{\\frac {1}{\\left(1+i\\right)^{n}}}}{i}}\\cdot (1+i)^{n}\\,=\\,A\\cdot {\\frac {\\left(1+i\\right)^{n}-1}{i}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/738f0ab7548b278ad51f00b7acee627057e53771" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.838ex; width:51.187ex; height:7.176ex;" alt="FV \\,=\\,A\\cdot\\frac{1-\\frac{1}{\\left(1+i\\right)^n}}{i} \\cdot (1+i)^n \\,=\\,A\\cdot\\frac{\\left(1+i\\right)^n-1}{i}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Example_6:_Price.2Fearnings_.28P.2FE.29_ratio">Example 6: Price/earnings (P/E) ratio</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=23" title="Edit section: Example 6: Price/earnings (P/E) ratio">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>It is often mentioned that perpetuities, or securities with an indefinitely long maturity, are rare or unrealistic, and particularly those with a growing payment. In fact, many types of assets have characteristics that are similar to perpetuities. Examples might include income-oriented real estate, preferred shares, and even most forms of publicly traded stocks. Frequently, the terminology may be slightly different, but are based on the fundamentals of time value of money calculations. The application of this methodology is subject to various qualifications or modifications, such as the <a href="/wiki/Gordon_model" class="mw-redirect" title="Gordon model">Gordon growth model</a>.</p>\n<p>For example, stocks are commonly noted as trading at a certain <a href="/wiki/P/E_ratio" class="mw-redirect" title="P/E ratio">P/E ratio</a>. The P/E ratio is easily recognized as a variation on the perpetuity or growing perpetuity formulae - save that the P/E ratio is usually cited as the <i>inverse</i> of the "rate" in the perpetuity formula.</p>\n<p>If we substitute for the time being: the <i>price</i> of the stock for the present value; the <a href="/wiki/Earnings_per_share" title="Earnings per share">earnings per share</a> of the stock for the cash annuity; and, the discount rate of the stock for the interest rate, we can see that:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>P</mi>\n            <mi>E</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mi>i</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>P</mi>\n              <mi>V</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mi>A</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {P \\over E}\\ =\\ {1 \\over i}\\ =\\ {PV \\over A}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/8a11cddbe7dca602d52c4616ae20b22639e794eb" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.005ex; width:17.561ex; height:5.509ex;" alt="  {P \\over E}  \\ = \\ {1 \\over i} \\ = \\ {PV \\over A } " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>And in fact, the P/E ratio is analogous to the inverse of the interest rate (or discount rate).</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>P</mi>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mo>/</mo>\n              </mrow>\n              <mi>E</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {1 \\over P/E}\\ =\\ i}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3e18447f52692139b268433f6baaf282b07657e8" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:10.634ex; height:6.009ex;" alt=" { 1 \\over P/E } \\ = \\ i " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Of course, stocks may have increasing earnings. The formulation above does not allow for growth in earnings, but to incorporate growth, the formula can be restated as follows:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>P</mi>\n            <mi>E</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mi>i</mi>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mi>g</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {P \\over E}\\ =\\ {1 \\over (i-g)}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/965101081aaea0e46bbdf88b6123788242710a39" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.671ex; width:14.349ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=" { P \\over E } \\ = \\ {1 \\over (i-g)}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>If we wish to determine the implied rate of growth (if we are given the discount rate), we may solve for <i>g</i>:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>g</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi>i</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>E</mi>\n            <mi>P</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle g\\ =\\ i-{E \\over P}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0a9f36e81387069b91ed9edd87bdefb0ff74c01a" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.005ex; width:11.683ex; height:5.509ex;" alt=" g \\ = \\ i - {E \\over P}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Continuous_compounding">Continuous compounding</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=24" title="Edit section: Continuous compounding">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Rates are sometimes converted into the <a href="/wiki/Continuous_compounding" class="mw-redirect" title="Continuous compounding">continuous compound interest</a> rate equivalent because the continuous equivalent is more convenient (for example, more easily differentiated). Each of the formul\xc3\xa6 above may be restated in their continuous equivalents. For example, the present value at time 0 of a future payment at time <b>t</b> can be restated in the following way, where <b><a href="/wiki/E_(mathematical_constant)" title="E (mathematical constant)">e</a></b> is the base of the <a href="/wiki/Natural_logarithm" title="Natural logarithm">natural logarithm</a> and <b>r</b> is the continuously compounded rate:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mtext>PV</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mtext>FV</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mi>r</mi>\n            <mi>t</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\text{PV}}={\\text{FV}}\\cdot e^{-rt}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3c8e603d067fffde5bf65fabe07e81bd7e162a22" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:15.389ex; height:2.676ex;" alt=" \\text{PV}  = \\text{FV}\\cdot e^{-rt} " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>This can be generalized to discount rates that vary over time: instead of a constant discount rate <i>r,</i> one uses a function of time <i>r</i>(<i>t</i>). In that case the discount factor, and thus the present value, of a cash flow at time <i>T</i> is given by the <a href="/wiki/Integral" title="Integral">integral</a> of the continuously compounded rate <i>r</i>(<i>t</i>):</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mtext>PV</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mtext>FV</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>exp</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \xe2\x81\xa1 --></mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          <msubsup>\n            <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mn>0</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi>T</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </msubsup>\n          <mi>r</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n          <mi>d</mi>\n          <mi>t</mi>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\text{PV}}={\\text{FV}}\\cdot \\exp \\left(-\\int _{0}^{T}r(t)\\,dt\\right)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/29b3cf7a4a9fe56af9cfe20e20cb2e867bef68df" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:31.12ex; height:6.509ex;" alt=" \\text{PV}  = \\text{FV}\\cdot \\exp\\left(-\\int_0^T r(t)\\,dt\\right)" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>Indeed, a key reason for using continuous compounding is to simplify the analysis of varying discount rates and to allow one to use the tools of calculus. Further, for interest accrued and capitalized overnight (hence compounded daily), continuous compounding is a close approximation for the actual daily compounding. More sophisticated analysis includes the use of <a href="#Differential_equations">differential equations</a>, as detailed below.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Examples_2">Examples</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=25" title="Edit section: Examples">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Using continuous compounding yields the following formulas for various instruments:</p>\n<dl>\n<dt>Annuity</dt>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>A</mi>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>e</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n                  <mi>r</mi>\n                  <mi>t</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>e</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>r</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\ PV\\ =\\ {A(1-e^{-rt}) \\over e^{r}-1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d24a6d883861c0c17ac8094288dd4f66908c64a0" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.838ex; width:20.81ex; height:5.843ex;" alt=" \\ PV \\ = \\ {A(1-e^{-rt}) \\over e^r -1}" /></span></dd>\n<dt>Perpetuity</dt>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>A</mi>\n            <mrow>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>e</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mi>r</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\ PV\\ =\\ {A \\over e^{r}-1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c9ca01d70efe46a60aed762570aa43edeea06358" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.838ex; width:15.339ex; height:5.343ex;" alt=" \\ PV  \\ = \\  {A \\over e^r - 1} " /></span></dd>\n<dt>Growing annuity</dt>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>A</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>e</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n                  <mi>g</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>e</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n                  <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                  <mi>r</mi>\n                  <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n                  <mi>g</mi>\n                  <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                  <mi>t</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>e</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                  <mi>r</mi>\n                  <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n                  <mi>g</mi>\n                  <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\ PV\\ =\\ {Ae^{-g}(1-e^{-(r-g)t}) \\over e^{(r-g)}-1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/30daf2ab0dc75e70f3575d221f1e49f14b9ca37d" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:27.595ex; height:6.509ex;" alt=" \\ PV  \\ = \\  {Ae^{-g}(1-e^{-(r-g)t}) \\over e^{(r-g)} - 1} " /></span></dd>\n<dt>Growing perpetuity</dt>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>A</mi>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>e</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n                  <mi>g</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>e</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                  <mi>r</mi>\n                  <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n                  <mi>g</mi>\n                  <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\ PV\\ =\\ {Ae^{-g} \\over e^{(r-g)}-1}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/60aafac19dd4517a9795c67f9e22f0a0cf7965e3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:18.716ex; height:5.843ex;" alt=" \\ PV  \\ = \\  {Ae^{-g} \\over e^{(r-g)} - 1} " /></span></dd>\n<dt>Annuity with continuous payments</dt>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mi>P</mi>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mtext>&#xA0;</mtext>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>e</mi>\n                <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                  <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                  <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n                  <mi>r</mi>\n                  <mi>t</mi>\n                  <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n            <mi>r</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\ PV\\ =\\ {1-e^{(-rt)} \\over r}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/41b91de3b36f364558576936c0e5bbe2f8a73df8" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.838ex; width:18.521ex; height:5.676ex;" alt=" \\ PV  \\ = \\  { 1 - e^{(-rt)} \\over r } " /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>These formulas assume that payment A is made in the first payment period and annuity ends at time t.<sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-9">[9]</a></sup></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Differential_equations">Differential equations</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=26" title="Edit section: Differential equations">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href="/wiki/Ordinary_differential_equation" title="Ordinary differential equation">Ordinary</a> and <a href="/wiki/Partial_differential_equation" title="Partial differential equation">partial</a> <a href="/wiki/Differential_equation" title="Differential equation">differential equations</a> (ODEs and PDEs) \xe2\x80\x93 equations involving derivatives and one (respectively, multiple) variables are ubiquitous in more advanced treatments of <a href="/wiki/Financial_mathematics" class="mw-redirect" title="Financial mathematics">financial mathematics</a>. While time value of money can be understood without using the framework of differential equations, the added sophistication sheds additional light on time value, and provides a simple introduction before considering more complicated and less familiar situations. This exposition follows (<a href="#CITEREFCarrFlesaker2006">Carr &amp; Flesaker 2006</a>, pp. 6\xe2\x80\x937).</p>\n<p>The fundamental change that the differential equation perspective brings is that, rather than computing a <i>number</i> (the present value <i>now</i>), one computes a <i>function</i> (the present value now or at any point in <i>future</i>). This function may then be analyzed\xe2\x80\x94how does its value change over time\xe2\x80\x94or compared with other functions.</p>\n<p>Formally, the statement that "value decreases over time" is given by defining the <a href="/wiki/Linear_differential_operator" class="mw-redirect" title="Linear differential operator">linear differential operator</a> <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">L</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {L}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9027196ecb178d598958555ea01c43157d83597c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:1.614ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="{\\mathcal {L}}" /></span> as:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">L</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>:=</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>t</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {L}}:=-\\partial _{t}+r(t).}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b899395eaca4f983eeb0a7e81cd10b23b41bf144" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:16.525ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\mathcal{L} := -\\partial_t + r(t)." /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>This states that values decreases (\xe2\x88\x92) over time (\xe2\x88\x82<sub><i>t</i></sub>) at the discount rate (<i>r</i>(<i>t</i>)). Applied to a function it yields:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">L</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x2202;<!-- \xe2\x88\x82 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>t</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {L}}f=-\\partial _{t}f(t)+r(t)f(t).}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d786adcc4e16a0b8982248b827716d4e1a4d6424" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:25.095ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\mathcal{L} f = -\\partial_t f(t) + r(t) f(t)." /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>For an instrument whose payment stream is described by <i>f</i>(<i>t</i>), the value <i>V</i>(<i>t</i>) satisfies the <a href="/wiki/Inhomogeneous_differential_equation" class="mw-redirect" title="Inhomogeneous differential equation">inhomogeneous</a> <a href="/wiki/First-order_differential_equation" class="mw-redirect" title="First-order differential equation">first-order ODE</a> <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi class="MJX-tex-caligraphic" mathvariant="script">L</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle {\\mathcal {L}}V=f}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/abdee8c5e2a4f644eb89e283e2a3446afe21e484" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:7.81ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="\\mathcal{L}V = f" /></span> ("inhomogeneous" is because one has <i>f</i> rather than 0, and "first-order" is because one has first derivatives but no higher derivatives) \xe2\x80\x93 this encodes the fact that when any cash flow occurs, the value of the instrument changes by the value of the cash flow (if you receive a \xc2\xa310 coupon, the remaining value decreases by exactly \xc2\xa310).</p>\n<p>The standard technique tool in the analysis of ODEs is <a href="/wiki/Green%27s_function" title="Green\'s function">Green\'s functions</a>, from which other solutions can be built. In terms of time value of money, the Green\'s function (for the time value ODE) is the value of a bond paying \xc2\xa31 at a single point in time <i>u</i> \xe2\x80\x93 the value of any other stream of cash flows can then be obtained by taking combinations of this basic cash flow. In mathematical terms, this instantaneous cash flow is modeled as a <a href="/wiki/Dirac_delta_function" title="Dirac delta function">Dirac delta function</a> <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <msub>\n          <mi>&#x03B4;<!-- \xce\xb4 --></mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>u</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>:=</mo>\n        <mi>&#x03B4;<!-- \xce\xb4 --></mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>u</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\delta _{u}(t):=\\delta (t-u).}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9f5dca3a6e9de2f4189cf48ebf21b734c988d63e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:17.257ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="\\delta_u(t) := \\delta(t-u)." /></span></p>\n<p>The Green\'s function for the value at time <i>t</i> of a \xc2\xa31 cash flow at time <i>u</i> is</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo>;</mo>\n        <mi>u</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>:=</mo>\n        <mi>H</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>u</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <mi>exp</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2061;<!-- \xe2\x81\xa1 --></mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>(</mo>\n          <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n          <msubsup>\n            <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi>t</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n              <mi>u</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </msubsup>\n          <mi>r</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n          <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n          <mi>d</mi>\n          <mi>v</mi>\n          <mo>)</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle b(t;u):=H(u-t)\\cdot \\exp \\left(-\\int _{t}^{u}r(v)\\,dv\\right)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d36aa1ab1a471ea1228298dcce2024ff08e87fea" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:40.526ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="b(t;u) := H(u-t)\\cdot \\exp\\left(-\\int_t^u r(v)\\,dv\\right)" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>where <i>H</i> is the <a href="/wiki/Heaviside_step_function" title="Heaviside step function">Heaviside step function</a> \xe2\x80\x93 the notation "<span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo>;</mo>\n        <mi>u</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle ;u}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/14c321a649bc0aed22d9318ba7c56395a5a58091" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.385ex; height:2.009ex;" alt=";u" /></span>" is to emphasize that <i>u</i> is a <i>parameter</i> (fixed in any instance\xe2\x80\x94the time when the cash flow will occur), while <i>t</i> is a <i>variable</i> (time). In other words, future cash flows are exponentially discounted (exp) by the sum (integral, <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mstyle displaystyle="false" scriptlevel="0">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </mstyle>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\textstyle {\\int }}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d96a8c4f864737f0a20e662b6a7607d110ff6792" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:1.428ex; height:3.176ex;" alt="\\textstyle{\\int}" /></span>) of the future discount rates (<span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mstyle displaystyle="false" scriptlevel="0">\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <msubsup>\n              <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>t</mi>\n              </mrow>\n              <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                <mi>u</mi>\n              </mrow>\n            </msubsup>\n          </mrow>\n        </mstyle>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle \\textstyle {\\int _{t}^{u}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/df93f5a9dd7b1b1b3158e8e7320ab5d6bb69b485" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.171ex; width:2.705ex; height:3.509ex;" alt="\\textstyle{\\int_t^u}" /></span> for future, <i>r</i>(<i>v</i>) for discount rates), while past cash flows are worth 0 (<span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>H</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>u</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mtext>&#xA0;if&#xA0;</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo>&lt;</mo>\n        <mi>u</mi>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n        <mn>0</mn>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mtext>&#xA0;if&#xA0;</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo>&gt;</mo>\n        <mi>u</mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle H(u-t)=1{\\text{ if }}t&lt;u,0{\\text{ if }}t&gt;u}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/bdb75557c33f89f313391d6000370e89c53ad3b5" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:31.124ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="H(u-t) = 1 \\text{ if } t &lt; u, 0 \\text{ if } t &gt; u" /></span>), because they have already occurred. Note that the value <i>at</i> the moment of a cash flow is not well-defined \xe2\x80\x93 there is a discontinuity at that point, and one can use a convention (assume cash flows have already occurred, or not already occurred), or simply not define the value at that point.</p>\n<p>In case the discount rate is constant, <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>r</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>v</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x2261;<!-- \xe2\x89\xa1 --></mo>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n        <mo>,</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle r(v)\\equiv r,}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/5466512e77380743d1e40c2995976a4c67c446e9" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:8.853ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="r(v) \\equiv r," /></span> this simplifies to</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo>;</mo>\n        <mi>u</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>H</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>u</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>&#x22C5;<!-- \xe2\x8b\x85 --></mo>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n            <mi>u</mi>\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n            <mi>t</mi>\n            <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n            <mi>r</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>{</mo>\n            <mtable columnalign="left left" rowspacing=".2em" columnspacing="1em" displaystyle="false">\n              <mtr>\n                <mtd>\n                  <msup>\n                    <mi>e</mi>\n                    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n                      <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n                      <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n                      <mi>u</mi>\n                      <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n                      <mi>t</mi>\n                      <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n                      <mi>r</mi>\n                    </mrow>\n                  </msup>\n                </mtd>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mi>t</mi>\n                  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n                  <mi>u</mi>\n                </mtd>\n              </mtr>\n              <mtr>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mn>0</mn>\n                </mtd>\n                <mtd>\n                  <mi>t</mi>\n                  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n                  <mi>u</mi>\n                  <mo>,</mo>\n                </mtd>\n              </mtr>\n            </mtable>\n            <mo fence="true" stretchy="true"></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle b(t;u)=H(u-t)\\cdot e^{-(u-t)r}={\\begin{cases}e^{-(u-t)r}&amp;t&lt;u\\\\0&amp;t&gt;u,\\end{cases}}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/145a271317afd2820450dec2aeb9522ea5d72ede" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:48.689ex; height:6.176ex;" alt="b(t;u) = H(u-t)\\cdot e^{-(u-t)r} = \\begin{cases} e^{-(u-t) r} &amp; t &lt; u\\\\ 0 &amp; t &gt; u,\\end{cases}" /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>where <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>u</mi>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \xe2\x88\x92 --></mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle (u-t)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/0261065396eb017bbad50bc0b07eb1e5f5d32d35" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:6.871ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="(u-t)" /></span> is "time remaining until cash flow".</p>\n<p>Thus for a stream of cash flows <i>f</i>(<i>u</i>) ending by time <i>T</i> (which can be set to <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>T</mi>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mi mathvariant="normal">&#x221E;<!-- \xe2\x88\x9e --></mi>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle T=+\\infty }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/099a84b34ffbff1c932dc08a3f02be1f48df3889" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.505ex; width:8.908ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="T = +\\infty" /></span> for no time horizon) the value at time <i>t,</i> <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo>;</mo>\n        <mi>T</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle V(t;T)}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/5994d8ae493ab5e7220fb11cdbf8e91a9855bf80" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.838ex; width:7.169ex; height:2.843ex;" alt="V(t;T)" /></span> is given by combining the values of these individual cash flows:</p>\n<dl>\n<dd><span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" >\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">\n        <mi>V</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo>;</mo>\n        <mi>T</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <msubsup>\n          <mo>&#x222B;<!-- \xe2\x88\xab --></mo>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>t</mi>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">\n            <mi>T</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msubsup>\n        <mi>f</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>u</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n        <mo>;</mo>\n        <mi>u</mi>\n        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>\n        <mspace width="thinmathspace" />\n        <mi>d</mi>\n        <mi>u</mi>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\\displaystyle V(t;T)=\\int _{t}^{T}f(u)b(t;u)\\,du.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3eb3dc8370d4d5ad5ebf28e0bc51b7b8ca4a97cd" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -2.338ex; width:28.679ex; height:6.343ex;" alt="V(t;T) = \\int_t^T f(u) b(t;u)\\,du." /></span></dd>\n</dl>\n<p>This formalizes time value of money to future values of cash flows with varying discount rates, and is the basis of many formulas in financial mathematics, such as the <a href="/wiki/Black%E2%80%93Scholes_formula" class="mw-redirect" title="Black\xe2\x80\x93Scholes formula">Black\xe2\x80\x93Scholes formula</a> with <a href="/wiki/Black%E2%80%93Scholes#Interest_rate_curve" class="mw-redirect" title="Black\xe2\x80\x93Scholes">varying interest rates</a>.</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="See_also">See also</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=27" title="Edit section: See also">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Actuarial_science" title="Actuarial science">Actuarial science</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Discounted_cash_flow" title="Discounted cash flow">Discounted cash flow</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Earnings_growth" title="Earnings growth">Earnings growth</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Exponential_growth" title="Exponential growth">Exponential growth</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Finance" title="Finance">Finance</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Hyperbolic_discounting" title="Hyperbolic discounting">Hyperbolic discounting</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Internal_rate_of_return" title="Internal rate of return">Internal rate of return</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Net_present_value" title="Net present value">Net present value</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Option_time_value" title="Option time value">Option time value</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Real_versus_nominal_value_(economics)" title="Real versus nominal value (economics)">Real versus nominal value (economics)</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Time_value_of_money&amp;action=edit&amp;section=28" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: decimal;">\n<div class="mw-references-wrap">\n<ol class="references">\n<li id="cite_note-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web">Carther, Shauna (3 December 2003). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.investopedia.com/articles/03/082703.asp">"Understanding the Time Value of Money"</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATime+value+of+money&amp;rft.aufirst=Shauna&amp;rft.aulast=Carther&amp;rft.btitle=Understanding+the+Time+Value+of+Money&amp;rft.date=2003-12-03&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.investopedia.com%2Farticles%2F03%2F082703.asp&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web">Staff, Investopedia (25 November 2003). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.investopedia.com/terms/p/presentvalue.asp">"Present Value - PV"</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATime+value+of+money&amp;rft.aufirst=Investopedia&amp;rft.aulast=Staff&amp;rft.btitle=Present+Value+-+PV&amp;rft.date=2003-11-25&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.investopedia.com%2Fterms%2Fp%2Fpresentvalue.asp&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-3"><span class="m